76561198142532639,Recommended,288470,23296275,"Posted: 30 May, 2016",all,Art3mis,"I must admit, I expected more of this remaster.I was so excited when this was announced that I immediately bought the game at full price (which I almost never do). The fact is, apart from a graphics update, the game offers little more than the original did. I am generally someone who enjoys the feel of the game more than the look, and for anyone who tends towards the same perspective, the Anniversary version is probably not worth it.However, I can say very little against the game itself; it is still one of my all time favourites. It's witty, intelligent, story-rich with plenty of side quests to sink your teeth into, and it offers a surprising amount of character development considering your controllable 'Hero' doesn't actually speak. You also get to kick chickens. My only niggles with the game itself are that you can only play as a male character, which I find limits my immersion somewhat, and that the camera occasionally refuses to do as you tell it. The quests are also very binary good/evil - no grey areas here. And the guards are totally fine with you wandering around opening fancy chests, but as soon as you try to steal a moustache from a bookshelf, OH NO THAT'S NOT ALLOWED.I am still glad I bought this version of the game. And as I would confidently say that Fable should be played by everyone, I can hardly not reccommend it."
