,Recommended,288470,12088736,"Posted: 13 September, 2014",all,BitGlitch,"Alright, so let me say I may be a little biased, because Lionhead has bribed me with all the sun shaft effects.Ok, so basically, this game is a graphical enhancement to Fable: The Lost Chapters. And for all these other people reviewing, they are downvoting because they expected even more stuff to be in the game, which I find quite stupid because the whole point of re-making games like this is so that people who haven't played it yet can experiance it where it looks even better, or for nastolgia's sake.Alright, so here is the basic run down of good and bad:GOOD:- All the models, animations (Some of these are still the origional), textures, and light FX have been redone- The game looks really pretty on the max settings, and some of the movement is even smoother than before- Combat is still massively fun- Stays true to the origional's everything, but they did add some outfits though- The game supports modding, and even gives a free DLC to get the SDK- They are releasing some new content packs to add more to the gameBAD:- When you save, it only saves from your last checkpoint, sometimes you have to redo a thing or two (not very game breaking though)- The eye's pupils are too big on some characters, making the game look a little awkward- Textures can sometimes be a little lower resolution than would be expected- Texture poping sometimes happens (Unreal Engine's fault, not the devs)Overall, I would have to recommend this game. All the people asking for this need to stop complaining about the little things, all of them will either be fixed by lionhead or by modders. I don't know about you guys, but I am having a great time.So overall, about an 8.7/10EDIT; They added keyboard and mouse support in menus. It could have been better, but its on par so I dont really view it as a bad thing"
