,Recommended,288470,12089521,"Posted: 13 September, 2014",all,stretchfox,"Quick fixes in this review so read carefully if you want a great play experience.Alright, so I've read all the other reviews and I agree with most of them; however, there are some easy fixes to most of the problems.  Yes, there is a stuttering issue that is incredibly annoying.  It is rough being able to run Crysis 3 on ultra and not being able to run Fable on anything.  To fix this - cntrl alt delete and set fable's affinity to cpu 0 only.  The game was originally designed during a time when almost everything only ever used 1 core.  This does fix the issue and it runs perfect after.  I have a gtx 780...it is not nvidia that is the issue.  Nvidia runs fine with this program.  The FPS problem people are complaining about are because they have both integrated and dedicated graphics.  If you have an AMD APU or 4th gen intel the integrated graphics should be fine and you won't even notice (I have a 4th gen intel and just leave it running off that).  If you are still having issues though,  ""just go to Nvidia control panel and select the Manage 3D Settings tab. After that “select Program Settings” and find Fable Anniversary and switch the game to your Nvidia graphics card"". quoted fromsegmentnext.combecause I'm lazy.The game is best ran with a controller.  I have a cheap logitech i use for my emulated stuff and it works fine.  If you are going to use the keyboard, it isn't too bad but it isn't anything like the original.  I think people don't like change and just love complaining.  It is what it is.  Another complaint I heard plenty of was the lack of ""video"" options.  There are some assumtions made by the developers, if you have a computer today it will be able to play everything from 2009 on max.  They have some distance and shadow options for slower computers.  Fine assumption for a port, I'm not complaining - graphics are amazing compared to the original.Overall - great port/remake.  Lots of new stuff to play with, higher difficulty option, amazing graphics that will stun you.  If you have the original, do a comparison just for the wow factor.  I'll give it a solid 8/10.  I'd give it a 9/10 to have my mouse back and a 10/10 if you didn't release it before fixing the bugs.  Although I'm sure they'll get fixed in the near future, I hate paying to beta test.  Recommended to all fans regardlless.  Enjoy the nolstagia.Update - Through the nvidia control panel I increased all the settings to max (had to add the program because it wasn't there originally), enable the option to allow/optimize multiple CPUs and this helped a lot.  I'm now running perfectly with all 8 cores firing.  There is no delay when skipping dialog now and everything is much smoother."
