76561198025478775,Not Recommended,288470,12108015,"Posted: 15 September, 2014",all,demas59,"Ok, so they have released a patch to fix some of the issues. The UI is still broken however. You still can't navigate though the menus with a mouse, nor can you reassign the (stupid) menu keys.  You can map more of the keys (note thats STILL ""more"" not ""all""). While trying to reassign the keys to something a little more sane I discovered you can't map anything to ctrl or alt, and that left shift and right shift are treated as the same key.  also the ' key is forbidden for keyboard mapping.  No idea why, it just ""is"". Oh, and ""accept"" and ""back"" are still hardcoded to ""A"" and ""B"".  Nice first try, now how about giving us a patch that actually FIXES the issues we're all complaining about.-- ORIGINAL REVIEW STARTS HERE --I wanted to like this game, I really did. I even played it past the intro level (which has an annoying about of cutscenes) in the hope I'd get used to the UI and controls. But this has to be the worst port I have ever had the misfortune to pre-purchace.  The User Interface is horrible, the ""new"" graphics are nothing much (and some of the ""new"" faces are appalingly ugly).  This is a quick and dirty port of a console version rather than a PC version.  How quick and dirty?  The ""A"" and ""B"" buttons from the joystick have been assigned to the ""A"" and ""B"" keys on the keyboard so they didn't have to change anything else.  Half the keys (and as far as I can tell, all the mouse commands) cannot be redefined, some of the special moves (flaunt, first person perspective when using a bow) either don't work at all, or work so sporadically as to be unusable. Quest markers for secondary missions are either missing or randomly vanish (and so do some guard quest NPC's, don't tell someone to wait then go kill bandits, you'll come back to find they have vanished and the quest is now unplayable).If there was a reasonable way to hand this back for a refund I'd be at the head of the queue.  Until they release a patch for at least the UI and quests, I'd advise leaving this alone and trying the older ""fable lost levels"" instead.  It's cheaper, and apparantly has a UI that actually works."
