76561198024398968,Recommended,288470,24146896,"Posted: 6 July, 2016",all,|SE|prome,"Not as good as Fable 1 & 2, but still a good game.I'm just gonna list the cons,1. The difficulty, dont play on the easy mode, you are practically immortal(with potions ofc). I didnt die once in a full playthrough. I never failed a mission once either.2. Optimization/Graphics, well its HD, it does look good. But, some animations lag. My system should be able to run 4 instances of this game at the same time. Dont get me wrong, its not a constant lag or anything, just some animations do lag, so I guess it isnt completly optimized.3. The interaction with NPCs, for example, if you want to have sex with your SO you'll have to court him/her alot. Then get married. Then court them again alot more before you can have sex. I dont really play games like Fable for the static 15 second moaning and a black screen, but still. And particulary Lady Grey, you have to court here like a million times. Literally.4. The short gameplay, mainquests took about 6 hours for me. In 13 hours I completed all sidequests aswell, including the 2 godly weapons you get from the 'good' and the 'bad' worshippers. I didnt get all Demon Doors and Silverkey-chests though, so I guess you can add 1-2 more hours if you include those.5. The money-making method, for obvious reasons, I'm not gonna say it here and spoil your potential gameplay, but did they really think this through, spend 1 ""skillpoint"" and be able to resell everything right after you bought it to gain gold? Thats uncool. But then again, you dont have to use it.6. Lack of buildings that you can buy. Also, you cant decorate your houses manually.7. Gear, the lack of diversity is absolutely ridiculous. The best weapons and armors is available for you after 10 minutes of gameplay. It doesnt matter that the town you start in has supereasy surroundings and the last places you visit has semi-powerfull enemies, they sell the same gear, for the same prices. Some items cant be bought, but only found through secret quests, which is a good thing.8. The controls, dont play this with your keyboard+mouse. This game, as all Fable-games, is designed to play with a controller.9. The story, its just dumb and dull. I'll shorten it alot so I dont spoil it. Someone kills your family. You get training to become super OP. Your joruney to seek out revenge on your familys assassins begins. No more, no less.I bought the game on Steam summersale 2016 for €5(+ €4 more for the DLCs). If Fable Anniversary was my first Fable game, I would give a bad rating, because Fable Anniversary isnt any more than a mediocre game to be honest. But as I've played the other games and really loved them, I'm able to see behind the flaws. Im glad I bought it at a saleprice.If you're a fan of RPGs, its a must-buy, but dont expect alot of it. If RPGs isnt your niche, dont get it."
