,Not Recommended,288470,12094466,"Posted: 14 September, 2014",all,Loraliel,"I'm not going to write a conventional review on this game but I will leave my thoughts after playing it for about an hour.WARNING: This will be a rant in most places, but I will do my best.What I liked:- The Nostalgia: This is the reason I bought the game, and in most places, it delivered, at least aesthetically.- The Graphics: This is a bit of a double-edged sword... They look impressive enough (certainly an upgrade) but there are issues.What I disliked:- The Voice Acting: This is only a small point I suppose, but something miffed me about it... Much of this has remained from the original game, which is fine, absolutely fine, but the very first opening cutscene seems to have been re-recorded or remastered or they've done something to it, and it sounds terrible. The actor does not sound enthusiastic about this heroic tale that is about to unfold, and not only that, the sound quality is awful. Not sure if it's a problem on my end but it wasn't terrific, and for an opening cutscene I would expect something to excite me about indulging in my nostalgia and playing one of my favourite childhood games again, but in HD - the concept grabbed me and I threw my wallet at them, I really wish I hadn't now and spent it on something else, and I will explain why in the next point.- The Menu, Inventory, etc......... : I have no idea who designed this menu, but I do not think they were human. It is just so fiddly, so much so that it irritates me too much to even want to play the game. You can assign things, sure, but doing that takes some real jiggery-pokery, a little too much if you ask me. It's like trying to crack the da vinci code, when all I want is to eat an apple pie from my potions and produce tab. It has NO MOUSE OPTIMISATION. This is the big one everyone is talking about and I feel it needs to be heard. The original game had perfectly fine mouse optimisation. To call the game a HD remake and not have mouse optimisation is absolutely mind blowing to me. I know HD more so focuses on the graphics, but if its a testament to the original, I would expect everything to be in place that was originally, such as being able to use your mouse to select things in a menu... When I loaded the game up I was all excited to get stuck in, but my heart sank when I tried to use my mouse and realised I could not. That was the point where I realised that this would be a bad port, and it was from the very start.- The Options Menu: You are able to keybind some things... When you actually get into the game, mind you. But not the attack function, block function or anything important... The controls are fine for me, as I said previously. I can get on with them fine, it's a perfect setup for me. But for other people that's probably not the case, it's definitely something that should be there, why? Because Fable: The Lost Chapters had it. You could keybind anything.It's a terrible port at the moment. I really hope that a patch is released to make things easier for people who want to enjoy it on their PCs with a keyboard and mouse. I enjoyed Fable: The Lost Chapters perfectly fine on my PC, in fact I have done at least 4 seperate playthroughs of the game because I enjoyed it that much. This was one of my main childhood games. I feel as if its ruined, all because of this console focus they have gone with. ""Play it with a controller"" some people are saying - no. Why should I? If you're going to release a PC port of a game, do it right. I play on a PC. If I wanted to play it on a console I'd buy the console version of the game. I don't.The Graphics: As mentioned before, there are issues. Nothing major, the graphics do look okay to me. They didn't exactly blow me away, but they are certainly an upgrade, which I appreciate. I am not technically minded about this kind of thing, so forgive me for my simplistic manner of explaining it. There appears to be blur on some of the models. Yup. It's like blurry textures, and eventually they fade back to being detailed again. Its weird. It's only a small thing, it doesn't bother me that much, but the fact that they can't even get the graphics 100% right and they're calling this HD makes me laugh. Oh yeah, and the graphics options do not give you much freedom to do anything either.At this point I am terribly disappointed and would not recommend to any like-minded PC gamers like myself. If you can enjoy the game with a console controller, fine. You will probably have a blast, but that menu is enough for me to put this game down until it gets fixed, if it gets fixed."
