76561198035847111,Not Recommended,288470,12089797,"Posted: 13 September, 2014",all,Bisgo,"One step forward, 10 steps back pretty much sums up this retexture.Unfortunately this is a rather poor Xbox One port, that removes all of the good aspects of the original Lost Chapters PC version. Mouse functionality is no longer available in menus, instead navigation is controlled though the Home, End, Insert & Delete keys. You then make a selection using the ""A"" (!?) key.Whilst basic key rebinding is available, the main abilities are locked and cannot be reasssigned - block and dodge are both set to the mouse wheel which makes combat really fiddly for mouse and keyboard. The control scheme was clearly designed for use with an Xbox  controller.The game seems to use built in FXAA that cannot be toggled off, which gives the game a blurry, unfocused look hiding a large amount of the  higher resolution textures.Until large improvements are patched into this game, save your money and play the arguably much better original that was actually designed to be played on the PC."
