,Recommended,288470,19917923,"Posted: 24 December, 2015",all,Pepsi_Vanilla,"If you enjoyed Fable: TLC, then you'll enjoy the graphical update with the Anniversary version. The fact that I still enjoy this game in 2015 is telling of how fun Fable actually is. It has a decent story, good gameplay, vibrant/detailed graphics, a fantastic soundtrack, a handful of mini-games (such as Fishing and the Arena), an immersive cast of British voice actors, and it has full controller support for anyone using an Xbox 360/One controller.That being said, if you didn't enjoy Fable: TLC when it first arrived, you probably won't like this one either. It's very much a casual RPG and it does show signs of being outdated with the limited size of Bowerstone and the activities you can do, and it there are a lot of NPC's that don't have anything to offer, so they essentially exist to rub your ego (the way they react depends on your morality).Overall, Fable Anniversary is an enjoyable remaster of an older title. If you've never played Fable: TLC, I'd recommend purchasing Anniversary when its on sale just to get a glimpse of what started the Fable trilogy (let's just ignore the Kinect version entirely). I'd give this game a solid 7.5/10."
