h the W or S keys, you can't select a choice with a click of the mouse or a strike of the enter key, esc doesn't back you out. The ""A"" key selects, the ""B"" key backs up, and you must use the arrows to navigate the menue...I shut the game off in discust after I maxed all the graphics settings.Launched the game a few days later with a controller attached. OK fine, if I have to use one in game I guess I can get past the total lack of propper key set support... Now that I'm in the game my dissapointment grows further.The original animations were fun and cheaky at the low rest and dated textures, having the exact same with new textures... Just feels cheap. It can look better, with propper screen shots, and there are deffinitely added foliage, increased resolutions, and so on and so forth but... The dancing shadows from the original are amplified in this version, and you get ""pop in"" loading. I know what you are thinking, my computer must be slow or dated. I can play Witcher 2 maxed with uber sampling and not have an issue, so it's not the machines capability although who knows if it is a compatability issue.Next up, the EYES. I should have said this first but if you played it I wanted you to wait a bit to know I agree heh. The eyes are so bad they take you out of the rest of the game. They make the people look like creepy dead little dolls from a horror flick. They never are looking at the person they are talking to but they do move around and seem to stare off in a direction that might contain the city where the person is that they are talking to, but never actually at them.... This is so bad that all I can do is laugh, laugh at it's complete and utter discrace it has brought to the first game and laugh at the fact I spent money on it...They updated it so the crows in the start don't give you experience, but didn't bother to update it so you could save at any time and shut the game off and not lose your place...I may keep playing it, I'm not sure... If you want to try Fable, I sugest ""The lost chapters"" it was a fun and fantastic game. This one? Unless you want to laugh at it the way you would a movie from the 80's that's completely serious but you just can't help laugh at how bad it is, then don't bother."
