76561198054766153,Recommended,288470,16676780,"Posted: 24 June, 2015",all,blackenedwhiplash,"Fable: The Lost Chapters has long been my all-time favorite game, one I could always come back to no matter how often and still have a lot of fun and find new things. So when one day I logged onto steam and I was given a coupon for I think it was 75% off of Fable Anniversary, the reboot of Fable: The Lost Chapters with HD and more extras, well how could I have said no? The day I installed Fable Anniversary and jumped right into the story, a wave of sentimental memories as well as newly influenced wonder washed over me. It was the same game that crafted my childhood, yet it was a whole new experience. The controls were almost exactly the same, the major differences being what buttons bring up menus, inventory, etc. and how to navigate the menus (like how in the original game in the menus the right mouse button was the back button but now it does nothing in the menus). It takes a little bit to break the old habits here but nothing that takes away from the experience. The sound quality is also better. I personally am especially fond of the sound effects of hitting enemies in this game rather than in The Lost Chapters. The blood looks a lot better and splatters more realistically. This game just takes an amazing game and makes it even better. If you like RPGs and/or Fable, you need this game in your life right now."
