,Recommended,288470,35066910,Posted: 19 September,all,ReBoot,"The game is exactly what it says on the tin: A fable. </review>Ok, that review sucks, doesn't it? You still know nothing about what the game does and why I like it. However, the whole ""Fable"" part is quite important. You see, the game oozes the fairy tale atmosphere. It manages to be a fable in the form of a game. Everything, from character design to writing to you being the hero makes clear that this is an interactive fable.Aren't you the hero in pretty much every RPG out there? Well, sure you are. But no game ravels in this the way Fable does. You are renown, the game revolves around that. Case in example: Trophies aren't (just) for you to look at. They're to run around with, showing off to everyone in vicinity. They're to brag about, to beat your personal highscore of how many people you've showed your trophy in the face of. I am a well-renown little devil.Speaking of the devil, the game has an excellent cartoonish/fairy tale depiction of good vs. evil. Instead of helping a ghost of a dead sailor helping his wife, you can just as well kill her. That makes the ghost disappear, solving the overall quest (getting rid of the ghost), and you get bad karma points. Those aren't just points! My dude has bright red horns, blue veins over the white face, red glowing eyes and he oozes an eery red mist. The best cartoonish evil depicion since Overlord!What else is there to say? Well, the game offers what you're used to from RPGs. You have stats, you have equipment including upgradable weapons, you can have a bard sing of your deeds, you have magic if you want to use it. The RPG aspects aren't ground-breaking, but solid. If you're into the whole fairy tale atmosphere and want to be the hero with a holy halo or devil's horns, Fable got your back.The boss fight of the main story is botched. A big part of the fight, the boss floats being unavailable for meele combat. Well, they have thought of dropping quite the decent bow right before that fight, but they haven't thought of warning me to put enough points into archery not to make the fight suck. Result: Fight sucked big time. Well, I had enough healing potions to brush my teeth with, but it was needlessly frustrating."
,Recommended,288470,13667940,"Posted: 28 December, 2014",all,PrjectFreelancr,"I couldn't wait to play this game when I heard they were going to remaster it. Fans have been asking them to do an HD remake for years. The gameplay is exactly how it was on the original game (animations and all) and the only thing changed are the graphics. A lot of the reviews are negative for this reason but the majority of the people who were asking for the remake to happen did not and still don't want the original gameplay changed. Yes, there have been some features in Fable 2 and 3 that would have been nice to have on the remake (better animations once again), but a lot of fans, myself included, wanted to play this game exactly as it was. We just wanted to see this great RPG in full HD glory and updated so it ran better, so if you were a fan of the original but wanted improvements on top of the HD remaster, this probably isn't the game for you to buy, but if you, like me, just wanted to see this game in stunning HD quality, this is a great game to buy.The only con I have is the new inventory menu. It takes some getting used to and I'd have prefered the original one, but oh well."
