,Recommended,288470,12795562,"Posted: 4 November, 2014",all,Mister Crowley,"Judging by what it was, and not what people wanted it to be, the original Fable the Lost Chapters was excellent, and is one of the most defining games of that generation.Fable Anniversary retians everything you loved about the original; the humor, the combat and spells, the alignment system, and all those goofy little quests and tasks. But the video quality is updated massively; the models are much better, and the textures really pop as opposed to the original. The draw distance is greatly improved, allowing you to see your enemies much farther away now too, which can be helpful. Also the audio is improved too, but its hardly noticable honestly, given that so much of your attention is usally focused on the game itself.Achievments now come with it too, giving incentive to finish all those things you never did in the original, or just giving you a reason to finish them all over again. Inluded in those is one for finishing the game on its newly implemented ""Heroic Mode,"" which among other things, removes exploits, makes enemies harder and removes resurrection phials, allowing for a much more difficult experience.The DLC for this game is nothing more than custume packs, which are fun to use, but a little pricy. Still, even these costume packs can add a little more to your experience without feeling out of place from the original, and can also result in hilarious screenshots.All in all, it's a fantastic way for fans of the original to experience it all over again, and for people who may have skipped it to reconsider and give it a go. It's by no means one of the best RPGs ever made, but its certainly unforgettable."
