,Recommended,288470,16616757,"Posted: 22 June, 2015",all,ThirdDegreePun,"I wrote a 1300 word review of this game which apparently surpasses steam's capacity for reviews. So, with much reluctance I present to you the dot-point summary of my masterfully fleshed out glorious review of Fable: Anniversary; an HD Modern Re-Release of Fable: The Lost Chapters;The Good- Expansive world which reacts to your decisions rather nicely- Visuals can be quite pretty in places (animations and models a bit uglier in other spots though)- Quick travel, mechanics and controls are quite good (set to classic. Seriously.)- Quests are varied, fun, and challenging when you 'boast'.- Humour is highly appreciated and nicely balances against the grittier elements of this game.- Play it in a bunch of ways, you'll probably be a mix of good and evil but tofu your way to goodness if you're like me.The Less Than Good- Bugs. Here and there. Can be rather annoying- Audio is too compressed for my liking- No female character available, your control over how they look is both expansive but also limited (e.g. hair colour)- Aging can be ridiculously fast. Its cool, but like, chill.- Some aspects of the game which would be fun (stealing) are hugely difficult.Fable: Anniversary is a game which has a wonderful soundtrack, excellent balance of darker elements with some tongue-in-cheek humour intersperced throughout, wonderful character-world interaction and an excellent quest and navigational system. It's held back by some distressing bugs and poor audio quality at times, but otherwise is a great romp into a classic RPG.8/10"
