,Recommended,288470,13220435,"Posted: 3 December, 2014",all,W1ntur,"I love the Fable games.  I bought The Lost Chapters (TLC) when it was released on steam out of nastalgia, but never got aroun to playing it.  Since this was an update on that version of the game, I came into this game blind to the changes that TLC made.I was disappointed at how many poor review this game was being given right out of the gate.  I preordered it, and was thuroughly enjoying it on release day.  I believe they did a wonderful job with this game, and were still patching any errors and exploits that were reported a week in.Personally I dissagree with the primary comlaint that was being given in the first week.  That complaint being about poor keyboard an mouse controls.  The original game was designed around a controller, and required significant changes to work intuitively with a keyboard.  They attempted this with a modicum of success, but as with any game that is designed with one control sceme in mind, they do not translate well.  I would never dream of playing this game without a controller, so in my opinion it is a moot point.The addition of a harcore mode was interesting.  It did not add much challenge though.  I almost never use potions, so the lack of resurection phails became the greatest dificulty.Overall I enjoyed this game even more than I remembered from my playthrough of the original.  I would recommend this game, but would also caution those with a tight wallet that there is little difference between this and TLC."
