76561198229231924,Not Recommended,288470,33683807,Posted: 20 July,all,teufel_barde,"Fable is the classic action rpg by lionhead studios, and can be described as a box of toffee. It takes a while to get through, its enjoyable in the moment, but by the end you feel ill and the experience isn't memorable in any way.The plot is as standard as it gets with fantasy stories. Your home town is burned down by baddies and you spend the rest of your life training to become a powerful warrior to stop the bad guys and help or hurt people. That is literally the entire plot in a sentence, there are no surprises in all honesty, or unique elements outside of the ability to be ""evil"" or ""good"". Even then, the being evil or good options boil down to ""want to be a complete♥♥♥♥♥♥"" or ""want to be the goody two shoes?"". There are some mildly amusing side quests, but almost all of them have been done better in other rpgs.The combat is pretty bog standard as well. You have melee (which is mainly one handed weapons, no shields, duel wielding), long range (bows and crossbows, which handle more or less the exact same), and magic (which has about 20 spells). The melee is simple, mash attack, use a guard break move when the enemy blocks, occasionally block or dodge, repeat. You will win 90% of fights this way without much issue. Range is basically useless unless you are fighting flying enemies, or if you want to pick off one or two enemies from a distance before they swarm you. Magic begins as tiny♥♥♥♥♥magic missiles, but can get really OP if you invest time into it. It never felt challenging, and I routinely did the ""no armour"" boast on quests just to add some level of difficulty. (I'll get to that in a bit.)Outside of combat, you can do gestures, this ranges from farting and burping, to pickpocketing and laughing like a♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ They all have their uses, but you don't really need to bother with them for the most part unless you are trying to get a wife (which can be almost anyone), or want to make people run away so you can steal from stores. You can have sex if you want, and you can break the game by buying and renting property to generate infinite gold. But ultimately, alot of the things you can do outside of combat feel pointless, they are there, and its nice that you can do these sort of things which means you can be whatever kind of person you want to be. But they feel like pointless fluff.That goes for most of the game actually. Alot of it feels pointless, as if the people writing this just didn't care at all, save for some dialog here and there, the way this game was written feels as bland and generic as it gets. Even the boast system on quests (one of the only actually good systems in the game) feels tacked on. You can take any quest from the guild you want, and boasts on top of that, in order to gain greater renown and more money. But its far easier to just farm the renown from enemies out in the world and get the money from renting out houses.Graphically speaking, it’s an older title, so it gets a pass on looking a bit dated, if anything it has aged well given how cartoonish everything looks. The music however is as forgettable as everything else though, not a single song really sticks out in my mind.Overall, this game was a disappointment. I beat this game on the Xbox a while back, and replayed it here, and I forgot how lacking this title was in, well, anything. I can't recommend it to rpg fans who want choices, because none of their choices really make a difference. I can't recommend it to any action rpg fans either, since there are far better titles like witcher 2 which do everything this game does but far better. It has no deep or thought provoking story to speak of either, so its more of a waste of time than anything. If you are looking for a quick, easy rpg fix without having to worry about micro managing anything, and don't care that the game has little depth, then you might want to pick this up and play it while you wait for another real rpg get your hands on."
