76561197976319123,Not Recommended,288470,24066666,"Posted: 3 July, 2016",all,Spacemanzero,"I would not recommend this game over Fable: The Lost Chapters, all it is is a graphical upgrade, no new mechanics, no bug fixes, nothing new that makes it worth the extra $24 you would be wasting on this over TLC. While it does look nice at a glance (and admittedly the glamour shots on the store page), in game it doesn't seem very good. While all the models and areas are remade, it all seems the same as TLC, they didn't even to redo the intro cutscenes, so they are very low-res and compressed while the rest of the game is HD. The animations each character does seem to be mapped to what seems like the TLC models and not the new Anniversary models, making the other cutscenes even worse to look at than Sonic Adventure's terrors. Now it might seem I'm making a big deal on graphics and animations, and you may be like ""What about the gameplay? Why are you just comparing to TLC constantly, can't you judge this as its own game?"". Well to answer your questions, the gameplay is exactly the same as TLC, the graphics and animations are the only thing they ""changed"" in this. Now if I were to judge as its own game, I would maybe say it's pretty ok, except for the weird animations and it will definitely not have aged well in a couple years (heck it doesn't even look that good now). But since this is a remake that is THE EXACT SAME GAME as the original game with a graphical upgrade, A comparison is all you can really review it on. And in comparison, TLC is better, though the graphics don't hold up as well to this, they have aged considerable better than this has in only 2 years, gameplay is the same, bugs are the same, story is the same. These were the reasons I found myself asking for a refund after such a sort playtime, I had seen all I needed to see and it wasn't worth it even if it was on sale. Just take your money and get Fable: The Lost Chapters, you'll be much better off."
