76561198037878832,Recommended,288470,12103626,"Posted: 14 September, 2014",all,thegreatdavid,"Before being disuaded from buying Fable Anniversary by the countless bad reviews, try comapring the time spent by playing by the people who didn't recommend to the people who did.It's important to remember that this is a remake of a console port. That said, if you buy Fable Anniversary without having played the original and you are expecting a AAA RPG adeventure prepare to be disappointed. Very few things are changed from the original game, aside from the visuals, and aside from the addition of extra weapons and armor from the pre-order bonus, there doesn't seem to be much in the way of rebalancing, save for the addition of the ""Heroic"" difficulty. Most people's gripes with the game seem to be from the controls and lack of mouse support in the menus, my recommendation is to have a gamepad. Believe me it will make life a lot easier on you.Storywise, the game is unchanged from TLC, become a Hero, take on quests, discover the secrets to your bloodline and the power that awaits you. Same old, same old.Visually the game does indeed look better than TLC, except for the face gen they used. Half of the NPCs look like their eyes are trying to escape from their head (lots of derp faces to be seen). The game does look more dark and grim than it did before, where it was more cartoony.Your biggest foe in this game isn't going to be the bosses or the small hordes of enemies, instead you will find youself fighting with control over the camera. If I can say anything bad about this game, it is that the camera controls have not aged well AT ALL! The bad camera controls are especially noticable in locked-on combat and questionable angles while you're gambling.Performance wise, the only real issue I have with the game so far is the occasional audio stuttering, my friend didn't seem to have this issue so it might be isolated to my rig, but it's still something that bugs me.Also if you're an achievement ♥♥♥♥♥, 18 hours of play was all I needed to get 100% of the achievements, so there's that too :P."
