76561198153176634,Not Recommended,288470,25387420,"Posted: 6 September, 2016",all,[YGS]Dies On Duty,"Let take a look at what Fable Anniversary did right and what did it do wrong. I will be reveiwing the game in a pro/ con style where i will try to give as much detail as i can with the game.Pro:The game has a really nice atmosphere. When playing i felt as if was playing a game like The Legend of Zelda Orcarina of Time. That really was cool to tap in to that sense of how similar in hero stories both are.If playing on chicken mode, the player can easily take on any challenges without much worry since that mode has many features that are gone on heroic. Such as the ability to get money really easy, revive potions, more hp, and the ability to take more hits.The achievements can be earned in diffferent ways, not all achievements but a good number can be earnd one way or another way depending on what the player chooses. One example was either winning the archery competition or pulling the sword from the stone nets the player the same achievement. This is awsome since it doesnt necessarily limit the player to do any thing specific that they wouldent necessarily do. Some people are either mainly archery or strength builds.Lots of content for both a good playthrough and bad playthrough. Note that there isnt much of a major difference but it does have some minor changes between being good and bad or whatever choices you chose in specific moments. They give dialog difference for the most part but can not really do anything majorily different. For an example i could kill wisper in the collesum or just leave her to live and after that nothing different besides dialog is different.Con:Enemies can easily block attacks and swing really fast. Thats ok if they do that only if i dont get major stun lock.Major stun lock. Like the point above the game has some major stun lock on the player himself far more than the enemies they fight. The collesum is the worst part especially when fighting the 2 trolls or gollems at the same times since if you get hit once better have your fingers crossed that you dont get stun locked to hell. I got stun locked so bad that i went from max hp to near death 2 times with no ability to change the outcome.The game at points does not explain things well. This goes for things like how to upgrade the archery skills and magic skills since the game doesnt tell you that 1 you can upgrade those skills in the same upgrade station and 2 the buttons to press to change the skill sets. I know it is simple but it is worth noting since the rest of the game explains things in good detail as to what this does and how to use it...ectHeroic mode makes getting money hard and causes an entire skill to be useless. I played heroic mode and thought it was ok for a hard mode, especially since it is hard to get money but heres the issue; there is a skill that helps with getting money that even if you upgrade provides no help what so ever. If it does nothing then why not delete the skill for that difficulty, sure it has a stealth ability for that one stealth section but really it doesnt help much at all in that aspect either.This game isnt metal gear solid so why do i need to stealth? I dont mind the option to stealth given if i want to be that player but it is a mechanic used once and done. It isnt even a good mechanic so why is it here? I know Orcarina of Time had stealth mechanics but that works since it wasnt a one and done thing. Also since i am talking about Zelda and stealth it worked in that game because it was for the most part simple and was not a huge deal since one can do it very easy since we can knock out the guards and pass through will ease. It isnt a big deal for this game but it is just an awkard mechanic to have when it is only used just once.The inability to abbandon a side quest. Sometimes when your not carful which side quest you choose you might choose a villain side quest which again doesnt mess with your moral very much at all but can really be annoying if you realize that you are going to kill guards or civilians making an area pretty empty later. This causes you to avoid the area like the plague but the problem is sometimes you need to go to the area to go to another area to do a main quest item. Which means the player will need to kill the guards and civilians to be able to travers in and out of the area without having to load a previous save. If the player could return a quest to the guild to abandon the duty then awsome. I wont have to worry about killing innocent people when i am trying to play a strictly good guy.Players can get villain quests at the guild...a guild full of heros. That is just akward and can cause people to acidently choose the wrong moral quests.Rpg elements mean pretty much nothing. As a maxed out hero i can be easily killable reguardless of how much damage resistance i have or how much strength i have. Some enemies take alot of hits not counting the big enemies but the normal minions. What is the main way to survive is to focus on weapons and armor. Kinda makes the whole idea of leveling up pointless in some way not counting the accuracy, speed, and all the magic skills pretty pointless.Wonky hit detection. Sometimes when you play the game you will take damage even though you dodge the arrow or sword swing. It is akward and can lead to some unfair deaths given the situation.The flopping hero (lol). At times when you take a hit, your character will be locked in place while the enemies move freely. This may be a bug or glitch but it is an annoying issue i ran into many times while playing heroic mode. Since the enemies have free movement they can constantly hit you while you can obviously do nothing. After the game releases your character from being immoblized, he will flop multiple times which looks funny but wastes time and can lead to more damage being taken or being stuck in a stun lock.Some bosses are just broken. Being broken doesnt mean unbeatable but just a real pain to fight because they have the ability to use magic. I dont mind that if it didnt do so much damage and they were always attacking which makes getting a hit in a real chore. The main one i feel is broken is the final boss since he has this magic ability to suck all the hp from the player. I dont know if this is just strictly heroic only moment or not but it is broken since the hp drops very fast and you die. It is unfair in the sense that you can not dodge it and if you dont have any healing items then your dead. The boss isnt too much of a trouble but that one move can make or break ones experience since it doesnt allow equality in other circumstances where people are low or have no health potions. All the other bosses you have a chance except maybe maze since he has the lightning spell that auto locks on which is again broken since you can not dodge unless your behind and object.Archors can pre-aim. So if you turn the corner in a hallway and get hit by an archor immediantly passing the corner. That is unfair since the player has no chance of avoiding it unless they dodge roll pass the corner but still there is a chance they will shoot it after the roll animation which will cause a hit. Not just that but enemies can fire arrows at you without looking at you. It looks funny but again can be really broken since if the player doesnt know that this can happen then they will get hit thinking they can rush the enemies to attack with the sword.Conclusions:Fable is not great of a game. It has really nice set peices but nothing really in terms of entertainment. There are weird bugs and glitches that can lead to some unfair and frustrating deaths depending on the difficulty. There was 2 pretty unfair bosses and other cons i put in the list. I am just too lazy to remention them again. I unfortunantly can not reccommend the game since i didnt really have fun playing the game and had issues with bugs and glitches."
