76561197985584880,Not Recommended,288470,32266705,Posted: 8 June,all,g.pelleon,"Never wrote a review on any of my 151 steam games, but I HAVE to warn others not to waste 32 euros based on completely biased reviews here. Every other review focuses on how Fable is their childhood and its an amazing game. Some think the remaster is good, some think its bad. But I just want to write a review about it being A GAME. A game release for 32 euros.TL:DR: If you are buying this only out of nostalgia, you belong to the only group of people that might enjoy this game. The remaster is still weak though. The Witcher III costs less than this... thing... There is no comparison, seriously. Also any other major RPG now and 10 years back has more value than this. There is very little content and the novelty morality and romance systems are a joke.Positives:Relatively speaking, compared to other RPGs on the market priced similarly - None. There are no actual positives. It has okey stylized graphics and the begining seems to be a start of something great... Its not though.Crushed expectations:SIZE: I thought the game is big, or at least comparable to other RPGs... Its not, even Morrowind has far bigger and FAR more interesting world and that was 12 years before this thing was released and 2 years before the original Fable was released. Every segment is tiny, and separated from others by a loading screen. Whats worse - the whole world is incredibly tiny as well. I thought the map will get bigger over time. NOPE. In first few hours, you have traveled through the whole map. To just walk the distance will take you like 10 minutes, INCLUDING the 20 loading screens. TINY!COMBAT: Attempted action combat, extremely simplistic. The only interesting thing is that there are quite a few spells, but most of them are not worth it. There are very few weapons in the game and they behave samey, only have different speeds and dmg. They also have mostly the same model recolored for different quality.STORY: I have to say, I couldnt force myself to finish the game. But the story didnt keep me interested too much. It might get better towards the end, but I wouldnt hold my breath. The main meat of the game is in the quests, that are... just there. On the map. You pick them, you go there... and then some story happens. The gameplay and story seemed to be completely separated. But the quests have an even bigger flaw:GOOD/EVIL SYSTEM: The game was hyped for the moral decisions you can do. Well, no. Its quests again. You LITERALLY get a pair of quests on the map - One for good points, one for evil points. Example: ""KILL THE FARMERS"" or ""PROTECT THE FARMERS""... Thats it. That is the morality system. The only other BIG INOVATION is that you can wear light colored stuff to be ""more good"" or dark to be ""more evil"". Also eating some stuff will give you good/evil points... like eating Tofu = good. Okey game, go home, you are drunk... Compare this to any serious title with actual moral decisions and you have to conclude this was made for small kids... But its not, sometimes it gets strangely dark, and you can gave PG sex... Which bring me to my next point:ROMANCE: This is the worst letdown for me. When I realized this game is small, has boring combat, uniteresting story and the morality system shouldnt even be called a system, I recalled that there was romance and even SEX in the game... The sad truth is, its even more simplistic than the ""morality system"". All you have to do (and CAN do, unfortunately) to get to the pinacle of romance = mariage, sex - is to get gold to buy steel armor (a few hours) and buy some chocolates and a ring. Than you go to town and spam romance emote on a woman. She likes you after you emote her 5 times in that armor. You then give her the chocolate. She falls in love with you instantly. You give her the ring. BAM you are now married. Now go to your house (yes you can buy propery, it has no function tho, it just EXISTS there) and you emote her some more. BAM sex scene (= 5 times the same voice track. Literally the same OH sound or whatever it was 5 times, like a broken recorder. All while looking at black screen for 30 seconds. Exciting). Thats it. There is NOTHING more to it. If you wanted, you can do all this like 2 hours in the game, just buy more chocolates/flowers, you wont need the steel armor set.I believe there might be a brothel somewhere later in the game,  but that most likely results in the same black screen with maybe some EVIL points added for good measure.OVERALL: The game cant compete with any good or mediocre RPG nowadays and it probably coulnt compete with good RPGs even 10 years ago when the original version was released. The lack of content is stuning. The recolored weapons just reminded me of Vanilla WoW, and even that MMO game used it only for crafted low-lvl gear. The morality and romance systems are a joke and seem almost insulting. Could be interesting for very young audience 10 years ago, but not now. The fact that you can get Witcher III or Skyrim for less... is incredible.Dont buy this as a game, only as a nostalgia token."
76561198053767780,Not Recommended,288470,30704397,Posted: 24 March,all,Anguis Furor,"Unbalanced nonsensical piece of garbage.3 Whole strenght based skill. Strenght (mediocre, pulled down by the ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ melee system), Armor (useless), Health(at least worth something).3 Whole dexterity based skill. Guile=Charisma/Stealth (useless), speed (next to useless) accuracy (actually useful)A bunch of magical skills. Timeslow, Multistrike, Heal and Mana is useful. The rest are useless.All of them are from 1-7 except spells, which go from 1-4.There are two melee attacks, a regular, and a charged attack, which can only be executed at certain times. Ranged attacks have to be charged. Some spells like Fireball can be supercharged, which will make them more powerful.Ther are four XP types. General, Melee, Skill, Magic. Each XP can only be spent on its own skills, except General, which can be spent on anything. Melee XP comes from hitting stuff in melee, Skill XP comes from trading and shooting stuff with bows and crossbows, magic XP comes from casting spells (any spell, as long as it hits a valid target. Like Fireball anyone, Healing always gives xp, since you are a valid target). General XP only received on killing the target, or at certain quest reward points. All XP rewards subject to the combat multiplier, except for the quest rewards.Story (so far) bandits ransack your village, killing everyone, except you, your mother and sister. Apparently you are part of some sort of ancient bloodline, who can do stuff because reasons. Then each time you finish the quest, you get a DEUS EX FAKLOGIC level help to continue your epic quest to save your family. Then you get captured, and tortured, and you have to play this part because the developers are sociopaths. I mean ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ly attempt to create emotional vestment which they miserably failed just like in the previous ten or so hours. I mean... okay, I give up, there is literally no reason to play through your own torture. This is where I 