76561198182540093,Recommended,288470,30478051,Posted: 12 March,all,Scomik,"So It's hard to rate this game honestly because today's standards for RPGs are so much greater than they were back when fable first came out, but I am going to rate it honestly by today's standards. I have also played the original and is probably one of my more favorite games for the xbox.Story:  5/10While the game is funny with a multitude of different side characters and side quests the game is overall short and does not immerse you well enough in to the world of fable. Since the story is short,  it makes everything seem to fly by, leaving  no real build up of characters and backstories, even though you can hear them briefly at the end of the game. The story does have it's twists, but at least to me, aren't super shocking and mind blowing.Gameplay/Combat: 4/5I do however enjoy the action combat. Nearly full control over what you can do, with no one type of combat (power,skill,will) feeling way overpowered, until maybe the last act of the game. The makers did very well in creating will powers that complement power and skill (personal favorite combo = slow time + multistrike + melee) making you not want to be purely a mage or warrior. This is an old game so sometimes targeting can be sketchy but overall a fun combat system.Replayability/Postgame:  0.5/2When you beat the game, you may have some sidequests leftover, but overall nothing extra once you are done. There is a little pull to create a new character and play the game in order to be the opposite of what you were the first time (good/evil) but its not really worth it.Graphics: 1.5/3This is an HD remake of the original so it the environment and characters do look nicer than it did in the original. However, it is not breaking any records and does not impress me to give it more than an average score.Music  0.5/2 -Not many tracks, Not really any standout tracks. Unique boss music? nope. Pretty much the music is there and the music fits the area you are in.Misc/Unique extras:  1.5/3Customization wise, I like that armor changes your appearance but the overall selection seems kind of small. There is no real benefit to wear cool or funny gear that you get because the armor values are much lower than the warrior plate armor, while at the same time the plate armor does not dull your mage abilities. The game being funny is definitely a bonus. I still like Fable's unique experience system (general/skill/will/power) where basically you get general experience and then bonus experience for whatever fighting style you did that battle. The new ""hard mode"" is another new pull that can get the hardcore gamers a little more challenge.Overall 13/25The problem really is the story has not held up over the years, and this is an rpg meaning the game score should be heavily weighted towards the story and that's what I did.  Gameplay is still solid by today's standards and should not be overlooked.based on the score  this game hardly gets a thumbs up but I' would give it a thumbs up because it is a game worth playing especially for nostalgia purposes. This game also played a big role in RPGs, helping lead the way to more decision based RPG games."
