76561197988113155,Recommended,288470,28814800,"Posted: 29 December, 2016",all,SAF,"I have very fond memories of Fable. It was the Fall of 2004, I was almost a year removed from my intense Morrowind addiction, I was living in my gay alcoholic uncle's basement, in debt, with a drama queen of a g/f, and then along came the release of Fable. It was very unique at the time because you could choose to do ""good"" or ""evil"" things to people (and chickens) which affected not only how NPCs reacted to you, but also your appearance (halo, horns, etc....).The soundtrack was incredible, it's what stood out to me when I first started the game, the main theme song was ""enchanting"" to me and I don't use words like that. The graphics were excellent and I think the artsyle still holds up today. Fable Anniversary has improved graphics (a bit), includes the Lost Chapters, and also added gamepad support, which was a win for me.Fable's story was well done and the combat and overall gameplay kept me entertained (expressions were fun), but the game was too short and a bit too easy. I remember beating it in about 20 hours, feeling accomplished because I had a lot of fun with the game, but also saying to myself, ""That's it""??? I was bummed.After I beat it, I missed the game dearly, I missed the freedom you had in the game, which was ground breaking. I missed my fugly wife I married in the game. I missed my Jesus-like, Mother Teresa type character I beat the game witth...I started a new game with an evil character, but never finished that game. I just remember my evil character kicking the s h i t out of every chicken in sight and going full hardcore gay with a male teacher. The groaning sounds they made when ""knocking the boots"" was hillarious!I am determined to play Fable Anni one day and beat the game once more. I highly recommend it to fans of Adventure & RPG. There isn't a game out there that is quite like it, besides for the sequels and Kingdoms of Amalur.I'll never forget my uncle crying and asking me ""Why, Why do I drink, Whyyyyyy!?!?!?"" and my good times with Fable during Fall 04...It's one of the few games I have played in my life that I'll always remember..."
