,Recommended,288470,29923156,Posted: 14 February,all,TwiliSailor,"A game that is overshadowed by it's own creators failings. Fable did not end up the game that we were promised all those years ago, but this remaster proves that it is still a great classic even today. It is a simplified or introductory RPG at its core, placing a much larger focus on dodging and attacking than on level ups and strategy. The shining points of this game are in it's lifestyle gameplay mechanics. Fable manages to add realistic elements to the game without it feeling out of place or panderous. This is the type of game that has as much focus on questing as it does on buying a house, finding a wife, getting fat and kicking chickens.Because these things are not forced on you in anyway, your decisions and action affect the character in a believable way. If you eat too much food you get fatter, if you need money you can rent out a house that you own. Doing a lot of evil deeds will make your character appear visibly more hideous and accomplishing more in game quests and side quests will begin to age your character and show how they have grown throughout the game.This remake includes not only the original game but also all of the content in the lost chapters. It has its moments of imperfections but they aren't an overall detriment to the enjoyment of the game. If you are a keyboard and mouse player however the lack of options compared to the original steam release are dissapointing."
