,Not Recommended,288470,33634941,Posted: 18 July,all,MoneyofFools,"Fable Anniversaryis a complete remake of the originalFableplusLost Chaptersexpansion in Unreal Engine 3. Knowing that, I expected Lionhead to resolve any technical issues or broken gameplay elements found in the original version. Instead it appears that the developer ported as much of the original source code as possible and focused on stability rather than imrpovement. There is little reason to purchaseFable Anniversary, as the original version is often found cheaper on Steam and features a UI actually designed for mouse and keyboards.This is a shame, asFable Anniversarywas a great opportunity to spruce up an aging classic. It is still an outstanding  take on clichéd fantasy RPGs. The tight gameplay, surprisingly human story, and amusing satire hold up remarkably well. Even the gothic fairytale asthetic retains an adimrable charm, but the updated visuals inFable Anniversarymay not gel with those who loved the original artistic composition.---My SpecsGPU - GTX 1070 SLICPU - i7 6700kRAM - 16GBsStorage - NVMe SSDOS - Windows 10My Graphics SettingsResolution - 2560 x 1440FullscreenVsync - OFFGeomerty LOD Distance - HIGHShadow Distance - HIGHLandscape LOD Distance - ULTRAAniosotropic Filtering - IGNORED (Forced 16x in Nvidia Control Panel)Extra EnhancementsReshade 3.0FXAA RemovalAltering the .ini to disable ambient occlusion and all forms of blur.My ExperienceI encountered no major issues while playingFable Anniversary. It worked well with third party programs and overlays. It never crashed, though it suttered at various points. Even when using an Xbox controller (which the UI was designed for), navigating the menus was tedious.Resources I UsedPCGamingWikiThe Fable WikiFelixanity's 100% Achievement Guide"
