,Recommended,288470,34019903,Posted: 4 August,all,Alex~,"Fable Anniversary is, in my opinion, simply a better version of an already great game. The graphics have been overhauled, the interface has been redone, a new difficulty added for veteran players looking for a challenge, achievements for achievement hunters, controller support and a multitude of Steam emoticons, backgrounds, and cards.However, it does have two pieces of DLC, but they are entirely cosmetic and new content, not anything cut from TLC. So, if you're a fan of the first Fable, or a series Veteran in general, and have a controller to play with (as the redone interface is built around the new controller support), you should definitely pick this up."
76561198043820407,Recommended,288470,34135148,Posted: 9 August,all,Daevid,"Honestly? Fable: The Lost Chapter was my favorite video game as a kid. And it stayed this was for long, long years. I played it probably, I don't know, over 30 times in the course of my teenage years? When I heard about Anniversary coming out, I was PSYCHED. I got it as quickly as I could. And honestly? I'm not disappointed. I mean, there isn't... That many changes, sure. And at first, it was glitchy as hell. But TLC ALSO was glitchy as hell, so I mean, it kinda was like the good old days. The glitches and bugs got fixed, it all went smoothly. The graphics are really good, the added difficulty level is a good plus for people like me who like collecting gameplays. Also the achievement are really cool, some are definitely hilarious. So, in the end, what I want to say is, if you like Fable, yes, IMO, this game is worth a buy."
