76561198054180809,Recommended,288470,35488250,Posted: 5 October,all,sapphirescales,"By far my favorite ""modern"" game ever (not counting classic consoles).  I've put probably 1,000 hours on this game including my XBOX (about 500 hours here on Steam).  Replayability itsn't very good, but the game is so excellent that you just want to play it again and again.  I know literally EVER nook and cranny in this game, every secret, every thing you can possibly discover.  Now I'm going to stop playing it and come back to it in around 10 years so I can experience it all over again.I will say this.  The character graphics in the original are MUCH better.  Sure they're not HD, but they were much better animated.  The characters look like dolls in the anniversary edition.  The only reason why I bought this edition is because it has full controller support.  I'm a PC gamer, but I prefer to use a controller.  Call me old school, but the last time I played a PC game that required a keyboard was in the MSDOS days.  Joysticks, off-brand unofficial controllers, and now the XBOX controller are what I use.  I don't want to memorize 100 different key combinations in order to play, and I typically play from bed so a keyboard isn't good for me."
